Process called "bitwise_xor" that takes left as String, right as String, left_type as String, right_type as String, options as Optional[BitwiseOptions] returns BitwiseResult:
    Note: Bitwise XOR (exclusive OR) operation
    Note: Result bit is 1 when input bits are different
    Note: Useful for bit toggling and simple encryption
    Note: Self-inverse operation: x XOR y XOR y = x
    
    Let result be BitwiseResult with:
        result_value as ""
        result_type as "uint32"
        bits_affected as 0
