    Let bit_width be 32
    If value_type contains "8":
        Let bit_width be 8
    Otherwise If value_type contains "16":
        Let bit_width be 16  
    Otherwise If value_type contains "32":
        Let bit_width be 32
    Otherwise If value_type contains "64":
        Let bit_width be 64
    
    Note: Normalize rotation amount (modulo bit width)
    Let effective_rotation be rotation_amount modulo bit_width
    If effective_rotation is less than 0:
        Let effective_rotation be effective_rotation plus bit_width
    
    Note: Handle zero rotation
    If effective_rotation equals 0:
        Let result.is_valid be true
        Let result.result_value be value
        Let result.result_type be value_type
        Return result
    
    Note: Ensure input value is within bit width range
    Let max_value be 1
    Loop with i from 0 to bit_width minus 1:
        Let max_value be max_value multiplied by 2
    Let max_value be max_value minus 1
    
    Note: Handle negative values by converting to unsigned representation
    If input_value is less than 0:
        Let input_value be input_value plus max_value plus 1
    
    Note: Ensure value fits within bit width
    Let input_value be input_value modulo max_value plus 1
    
    Note: Perform left rotation using shift and OR operations
    Note: Left rotation = (value << rotation) | (value >> (width - rotation))
    
    Note: Calculate left shift part (value << effective_rotation)
    Let left_shift_multiplier be 1
    Loop with i from 0 to effective_rotation minus 1:
        Let left_shift_multiplier be left_shift_multiplier multiplied by 2
    Let left_shifted be input_value multiplied by left_shift_multiplier
    
    Note: Mask to keep only the lower bit_width bits
    Let left_shifted be left_shifted modulo max_value plus 1
    
    Note: Calculate right shift part (value >> (bit_width - effective_rotation))
    Let right_shift_amount be bit_width minus effective_rotation
    Let right_shift_divisor be 1
    Loop with i from 0 to right_shift_amount minus 1:
        Let right_shift_divisor be right_shift_divisor multiplied by 2
    Let right_shifted be input_value divided by right_shift_divisor
    
    Note: Combine left and right parts using OR operation
    Let rotated_value be 0
    
    Note: OR the two parts together bit by bit
    Loop with bit_pos from 0 to bit_width minus 1:
        Let bit_divisor be 1
        Loop with j from 0 to bit_pos minus 1:
            Let bit_divisor be bit_divisor multiplied by 2
        
        Note: Get bit from left shifted value
        Let left_quotient be left_shifted divided by bit_divisor
        Let left_bit be left_quotient modulo 2
        
        Note: Get bit from right shifted value
        Let right_quotient be right_shifted divided by bit_divisor
        Let right_bit be right_quotient modulo 2
        
        Note: OR the bits (either bit being 1 makes result 1)
        Let result_bit be 0
        If left_bit equals 1 Or right_bit equals 1:
            Let result_bit be 1
        
        Note: Add result bit to final value
        If result_bit equals 1:
            Let bit_contribution be 1
            Loop with k from 0 to bit_pos minus 1:
                Let bit_contribution be bit_contribution multiplied by 2
            Let rotated_value be rotated_value plus bit_contribution
    
    Note: Convert result back to decimal string
    If rotated_value equals 0:
        Let result.result_value be "0"
    Otherwise:
        Let temp_value be rotated_value
        Let digit_stack be ""
        
