    Return result

Process called "rotate_right" that takes value as String, rotation_amount as Integer, value_type as String returns BitwiseResult:
    Note: Right circular rotation (bits wrap around)
    Note: No bits are lost - they wrap from right to left
    Note: Inverse of left rotation by same amount
    
    Note: Right rotation is equivalent to left rotation by (bit_width - rotation_amount)
    Note: This is more efficient than implementing the same logic twice
    
    Note: Get bit width from value type
    Let bit_width be 32
    If value_type contains "8":
        Let bit_width be 8
    Otherwise If value_type contains "16":
        Let bit_width be 16  
    Otherwise If value_type contains "32":
        Let bit_width be 32
    Otherwise If value_type contains "64":
        Let bit_width be 64
    
    Note: Convert right rotation to equivalent left rotation
    Let equivalent_left_rotation be bit_width minus rotation_amount modulo bit_width
    If equivalent_left_rotation is less than 0:
        Let equivalent_left_rotation be equivalent_left_rotation plus bit_width
    
    Note: Call rotate_left with the equivalent amount
    Let result be rotate_left with value, equivalent_left_rotation, value_type
    
    Note: Update operation name in result
    Let result.operation be "rotate_right"
    
    Return result

